Lotion Play is a subset of the better known [[Wet and messy fetishism|Wet-And-Messy fetish]] [[Wet and messy fetishism|(WAM)]], which typically involves participants using food (such as pudding or whipped cream), mud, or paint as a lubricant to facilitate sexual activity. Lotion Play isolates lotion specifically as a lubricating medium - setting it apart in the Wet-and-Messy genre, as other common WAM mediums do not have such specific popularity as Lotion Play.  {{nihongo|'''Lotion Play'''|ローションプレイ|rōshon purei}}, also known as gookkake, gluekkake, is a popular [[sexual fetish|fetish]], form of [[pornography in Japan|Japanese erotica]] and [[prostitution in Japan|prostitution]] request involving the use of copious amounts of [[personal lubricant|lubricant]], which in the [[Japanese language]] is referred to by the Old-French word "lotion" (ローション in Japanese).Typically lotion play involves a participant rubbing lotion on another using their body,<ref>Talmadge, Eric. ''Getting Wet: Adventures in the Japanese Bath''. Tokyo: Kodansha International, 2006, p. 187, 190–191. {{ISBN|978-4-7700-3020-7}}.</ref> [[sexual intercourse]] in a pool or bath filled with lotion,<ref name=pink>Sinclair, Joan. ''Pink Box: Inside Japan's Sex Clubs'', Harry N. Abrams, Inc., 2006, p. 112–113. {{ISBN|978-0-8109-9259-7}}.</ref> or lotion being poured over the participants during sex. In Japan (and other parts of the world), lotion is available in concentrated form (e.g.: liter/gallon) which can be added to hot water to produce the desired amount of lotion. A 1-gallon concentrate will typically yield 6-10 gallons of lotion (J-Lube Lotion Concentrate).  The main component in most lotion is [[Sodium polyacrylate|polyacrylate]].<ref name=lotion>[http://www.e-nls.com/pict2-2642-1111 Page for a lotion product, listing acrylate as the main component] (in Japanese)</ref> A similar effect can be achieved by dissolving powdered [[methyl cellulose]] in water.

